{{Infobox person | name = Dorila Antommarchi | image = | image_size = 180px | caption = Dorila Antommarchi | birth_date = 1850s | birth_place = [[Cúcuta]], [[Colombia]] | death_date = 1923 | death_place = [[Cúcuta]], [[Colombia]] | occupation = [[Poet]] | spouse = Milcíades de Rojas}}
'''Dorila Antommarchi de Rojas''' (born 1850s, [[Cúcuta]], [[Colombia]]) published numerous poems and sometimes used the [[pseudonym]] Colombiana. All her poems appear in various [[anthologies]]. Her sisters, [[Hortensia Antommarchi]] and [[Elmira Antommarchi]], were also published poets.
She died in 1923 in her native [[Cúcuta]].<ref>Isaacs, Jorge; Cristina, María Teresa. "Obras completas"; {{ISBN|958-710-107-3}}, {{ISBN|978-958-710-107-2}} (2005) [https://books.google.com/books?id=z3McUb-uhVMC&printsec=frontcover]</ref><ref>[http://laslagunasvillage.blogspot.com/2008_02_01_archive.html "Las Lagunas Village", 23 February 2008]</ref><ref>Rodríguez-Arenas, Flor María, "Bibliografía de la literatura colombiana del siglo XIX"; {{ISBN|987-1136-46-3}}, {{ISBN|978-987-1136-46-9}} (2006) [https://books.google.com/books?id=FRBjoRcjuoIC&printsec=frontcover]</ref><ref>[http://www.worldcat.org/wcpa/ow/213795210 Antommarchi Sisters, ''Poesías'', 1930]</ref>
