| below = Source: [[Police in Sweden]]<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.svt.se/nyheter/inrikes/siffrorna-visar-kraftig-okning-av-dodsskjutningar|title=Siffrorna visar: Kraftig ökning av dödsskjutningar|last=Nyheter|first=SVT|date=|work=SVT Nyheter|access-date=25 January 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180120024711/https://www.svt.se/nyheter/inrikes/siffrorna-visar-kraftig-okning-av-dodsskjutningar|archive-date=20 January 2018|dead-url=|language=sv}}</ref>}}

Sweden witnessed a steep increase in gun violence in males aged 15 to 29 in the two decades prior to 2018, in addition to a rising trend in gun violence there was also a high rate of gun violence in Sweden compared to other countries in [[Western Europe]].<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Sturup|first=Joakim|last2=Rostami|first2=Amir|last3=Mondani|first3=Hernan|last4=Gerell|first4=Manne|last5=Sarnecki|first5=Jerzy|last6=Edling|first6=Christofer|date=2018-05-07|title=Increased Gun Violence Among Young Males in Sweden: a Descriptive National Survey and International Comparison|url=https://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/s10610-018-9387-0|journal=European Journal on Criminal Policy and Research|language=en|volume=|pages=1–14 / Conclusions|doi=10.1007/s10610-018-9387-0|issn=0928-1371|via=}}</ref> According to a report published by academic researchers in 2017, shooting incidents with fatal outcomes are about 4 to 5 times as common in Sweden compared to neighbouring countries such as [[Germany]] and [[Norway]] when taking population size into account. The city with the highest prevalence of shootings was [[Malmö]]. The grave violence in the studied period also changed character, from criminal [[motorcycle gangs]] to city suburbs.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://sverigesradio.se/sida/artikel.aspx?programid=103&artikel=6770056|title=Fler skjutningar i Sverige än i många andra länder - P4 Stockholm|last=Radio|first=Sveriges|access-date=12 September 2017}}</ref><ref name=":4">{{Cite news|url=http://www.dn.se/nyheter/sverige/studie-fler-skjutningar-i-sverige-an-i-manga-andra-lander/|title=Studie: Fler skjutningar i Sverige än i många andra länder - DN.SE|date=5 September 2017|work=DN.SE|access-date=12 September 2017|language=sv-se}}</ref>

