'''''UQ Holder!''''' (later titled '''''UQ Holder!: Magister Negi Magi! 2'''''<ref name="subtitle">{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/daily-briefs/2016-10-07/uq-holder-manga-adds-magister-negi-magi-2-subtitle/.107381|title=UQ Holder Manga Adds 'Magister Negi Magi 2' Subtitle|date=October 7, 2016|website=[[Anime News Network]]|accessdate=October 8, 2016}}</ref>)  is a manga series by [[Ken Akamatsu]]. Set several generations later in the world of his previous work ''[[Negima! Magister Negi Magi]]'', it follows the adventures of a young boy who is transformed into a vampire and joins a secret society composed of immortal beings.

{{nihongo|UQ|ユーキュー|Yūkyū}} stands for {{nihongo|'''悠久'''|||"eternity"}}, the [[kanji]] that entwines inside the UQ logo, which alludes to the immortal nature of the characters.

==Plot==
Tōta Konoe, the grandson of [[Negi Springfield]], aspires to leave his village and live life in the city of Shin-Tokyo which has a tower structure rising into space. When he is mortally wounded by a bounty hunter coming after his guardian Yukihime's life, he discovers that he has been made into an immortal vampire by Yukihime, who is actually a 700-year-old vampire mage [[Evangeline A.K. McDowell]]. Picking up another boy named Kuromaru along the way, they go to a place outside Shin-Tokyo where Yukihime leads a secret society of immortals called UQ Holder.

==Characters==

===UQ Holder===
UQ Holder is a secret organization of immortals and ''[[yokai]]'' led by Yukihime. Its members reside at the ''Senkyokan'' (trans. "Fairyland Manor") estate, 10&nbsp;km from the Shin-Tokyo coast, which fronts as a hot springs resort. Its main members are known as Numbers. Its goals are to protect other immortals living in the Earth,{{Ref|Chapter|Ch. 7, 11}} as well as helping the outcasts of society.{{Ref|Chapter|Vol. 2, 4}} It is also interested in protecting humans from the immortals that are intent on destroying the society.{{Ref|Chapter|Vol. 5}}

;{{nihongo|{{va|Tōta Konoe}}|近衛 刀太|Konoe Tōta}} <!-- Tōta's name has macrons in the Kodansha USA version, see sample https://kodanshacomics.com/series/uq-holder/ -->
: {{voiced by|Yuka Takakura<ref name="Anime News Network">{{cite news|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2017-03-17/uq-holder-tv-anime-reveals-october-debut-visual-cast-staff/.113593|title=UQ Holder! TV Anime Reveals October Debut, Visual, Cast, Staff|work=Anime News Network|date=March 18, 2017|accessdate=March 17, 2017}}</ref>|[[Brittney Karbowski]]<ref name="English Cast List">{{cite news|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2018-10-16/uq-holder-anime-english-dub-cast-announced/.138249|title=UQ Holder! Anime's English Dub Cast Announced|work=Anime News Network|date=October 16, 2018|accessdate=October 16, 2018}}</ref>}}
: Tōta is a 14-year-old boy who was raised by Yukihime after his parents died two years prior in a car accident. His grandfather was assumed to be the legendary magician [[List of Negima! Magister Negi Magi characters#Negi Springfield|Negi Springfield]],{{Ref|Chapter|Ch. 1}} At the start of the series, when he is mortally wounded by an assassin while protecting Yukihime, he discovers he had been transformed by her into a vampire and then drinks her blood to affirm his immortality.{{Ref|Chapter|Ch. 1}} His dream is to be worthy to ascend Amanomihashira, the tower in Shin-Tokyo which leads into outer space. He would like to be a singer to support his friend in a band, but has a horrible singing voice, and is disillusioned that he won't be able to develop a [[Adam's apple|deeper voice]] or grow taller now that he is immortal.{{Ref|Chapter|Ch. 2}} Although immortal, he cannot regenerate severed limbs if the limb still has some life in it.{{Ref|Chapter|Ch. 8}} Within the UQ Holder group, he is member number 7.{{Ref|Chapter|Ch. 11}} Tōta uses a gravity blade, a sword that can adjust its weight thousand-timesfold or more.{{Ref|Chapter|Ch. 9}} He also has the power of "Magia Erebea", allowing him to absorb magic into his own body, bonding it to his soul.{{Ref|Chapter|Ch. 22-24}} In Volume 7, it is revealed that he was not a descendant of Negi's but a clone of him.{{Ref|Chapter|Vol. 7}} It is later revealed that his DNA was made of Negi's and [[List of Negima! Magister Negi Magi characters#Asuna Kagurazaka|Asuna Kagurazaka]].{{volume needed|date=October 2017}} :

;{{nihongo|{{va|Yukihime|Evangeline}}|雪姫}} <!-- Yukihime is common name, but she's also established as Evangeline -->
: {{voiced by|[[Yuki Matsuoka]]<ref name="Anime News Network 2">{{cite news|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2017-06-06/uq-holder-anime-casts-yuki-matsuoka-yuki-hirose-rina-satou/.117117|title=UQ Holder! Anime Casts Yuki Matsuoka, Yūki Hirose, Rina Satou|work=Anime News Network|date=June 7, 2017|accessdate=June 6, 2017}}</ref>|Heidi Hinkel (Yukihime), Shanae'a Moore (Evangeline A.K. McDowell)<ref name="English Cast List" />}}
: [[List of Negima! Magister Negi Magi characters#Evangeline A.K. McDowell|Evangeline A.K. McDowell]] is a 700-year-old vampire who, after parting ways with her friends from the Mahora Academy, she adopted the alias "Yukihime" and established the secret "UQ Holder" society for immortal beings. She appears as a tall and attractive woman with white blonde hair and blue eyes, although she can assume her true form of a 10-year-old girl on occasion.{{Ref|Chapter|Ch. 1-3, 30}} She becomes Tōta's guardian after she was allegedly involved in a car accident that killed his birth parents, but their dying wish was to have Tota survive and she transforms him into a vampire. At the start of the series, she is a teacher in a small village school, but later takes Tōta into the city and on their adventures.{{Ref|Chapter|Ch. 1}} Later, it is revealed that she had met Tōta centuries before becoming his guardian due to a [[temporal paradox]] and bonded with him at that time, implying that she also fell in love with him at the occasion.{{volume needed|date=September 2018}} She also still harbors feelings for Negi but claims that she intends to uphold her promise to him of ending his life should the Lifemaker succeed in taking over his body.{{volume needed|date=September 2018}} Later, it is revealed by Dana through a picture that in the original dimension from ''Negima'', Evangeline married Nagi Springfield after he was freed from Ialda's control by Negi.{{Ref|Chapter|Ch. 141}}

;{{nihongo|{{va|Kurōmaru Tokisaka}}|時坂 九郎丸|Tokisaka Kurōmaru}} <!-- Kurōmaru's name has macrons in the Kodansha USA version, see sample https://www.amazon.com/dp/B00KRO0D0G  -->
: {{voiced by|Yūki Hirose<ref name="Anime News Network 2"/>|Kalin Coates<ref name="English Cast List" />}}
: A member of the ''fushigari'' (immortal hunters) clan, Kurōmaru has been immortal for about 4 1/2 years before meeting Tōta.{{Ref|Chapter|Ch. 9}} He has black hair styled in black twin tails and his bangs typically cover over his left eye. Kuromaru's mission was to slay Yukihime or never return, but after losing to Tōta, he joins him and Yukihime on their adventures. Despite claiming to be a boy, Kurōmaru has shy mannerisms such as covering his chest that Tōta and others often confuse him to be a girl.{{Ref|Chapter|Ch. 3-6}} Kurōmaru later reveals that he comes from a tribe of demi-humans called ''yata ga karasu'' (crow in Japanese mythology)<!-- footnote in chapter 16 in English manga --> who are born genderless but can choose their gender at age 16 or naturally settle into one.{{Ref|Chapter|Ch. 16}} Although Kurōmaru wants to be Tōta's brother-in-arms, Kurōmaru develops romantic feelings towards Tōta, and Kurōmaru's body slowly transforms toward the feminine side despite not being age 16 yet.{{Ref|Chapter|Ch. 101}} Kurōmaru is an adept of the Kyoto Shinmei-ryū sword style and other Eastern battle techniques.{{Ref|Chapter|Ch. 3}}

;{{nihongo|{{vanchor|Gengorō Makabe}}|真壁 源五郎|Makabe Gengorō}} <!-- anime profile 10 -->
: {{voiced by|[[Yūki Kaji]]|Houston Hayes<ref name="English Cast List" />}}
: Gengorō Makabe is member number 6 in UQ Holder; he has short hair and wears glasses.{{Ref|Chapter|Ch. 28}} Not much is known about Gengorō Makabe's background or his immortality powers, but it is hinted that they are somehow video game-related, as he has a limited number of extra lives, that allow him to revive instantly after dying. He can also summon several weapons instantly and evaluate his opponents' like a game character's stats. He ends up using all his extra lives to help the rest of UQ Holder to stop a terrorist attack, thus losing his immortality.{{Ref|Chapter|Ch. 146}}

;{{nihongo|{{vanchor|Karin Yuuki}}|結城夏凛|Yūki Karin}} <!-- anime profile 05 -->
: {{voiced by|[[Yui Ogura]]<ref name="Anime News Network 2"/>|Molly Searcy<ref name="English Cast List" />}}
: Member number 4 in UQ Holder and nicknamed the Saintess of Steel, {{Ref|Chapter|Vol. 3 profile, Ch. 20}} Karin is a quiet girl around the same appearance in age as Tōta and Kurōmaru, Karin Yuuki is very devoted to Yukihime after having been saved by her in the past and is immediately jealous of Tōta's close relationship with her.{{Ref|Chapter|Ch. 10}} She often wears a schoolgirl uniform from Amano-Mihashira Academy after having infiltrated the school during a mission.{{Ref|Chapter|Ch. 43, 44}} She bears a tattoo on her back of the roman numeral XIII.{{Ref|Chapter|Ch. 14}}  Her immortality is said to come from divine origin, as all her wounds heal instantly without scars.{{Ref|Chapter|Ch. 14}} Centuries ago, she was branded as a witch and hunted when she was a small child. Her name was Yseut Karin Orte.{{Ref|Chapter|Ch. 20}} <!-- , based on the biblical [[Judas Iscariot]] -->

;{{nihongo|{{vanchor|Ikkū Ameya|Ikku}}|飴屋 一空|Ameya Ikkū}} <!-- anime profile 08 -->
: {{voiced by|[[Tetsuya Kakihara]]<ref name="ANN3">{{cite web|title=UQ Holder Anime Reveals 5 More Cast Members, October 2 Premiere|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2017-09-01/uq-holder-anime-reveals-5-more-cast-members-october-2-premiere/.120829|website=Anime News Network|accessdate=September 1, 2017|date=September 1, 2017}}</ref>|Adam Gibbs<ref name="English Cast List" />}}
: Contrary to the other members who achieved immortality through magical means, Ikkū Ameya obtained his by replacing almost all of his body with cybernetic implants,{{Ref|Chapter|Ch. 32}} which not only give him enhanced strength and speed, but several types of weaponry at his disposal, including the "Al-Iskandariya Orbital Cannon" which used to be Chachamaru Karakuri's pactio weapon in ''Negima!''.{{volume needed|date=December 2017}} He can also change his appearance by just transferring himself to a different cybernetic body with other physical features.{{Ref|Chapter|Vol. 5}} He appears as a 24-year-old and claims to behave like as a teenager, having entered a coma when he was 13, and being bedridden for 72 years before given a cybernetic body. He is member number 10.{{Ref|Chapter|Ch. 28, 32}}

;{{nihongo|{{vanchor|Jinbei Shishido}}|宍戸 甚兵衛|Shishido Jinbei}} <!-- anime profile 09 -->
: {{voiced by|[[Shunsuke Sakuya]]<ref name="ANN3"/>|[[Jay Hickman (actor)|Jay Hickman]]<ref name="English Cast List" />}}
: Member number 2 of UQ Holder, Jinbei Shishido is introduced as having dwelled in the underground tunnels under the facility for two years, after being sent there for having drunk Yukihime's wine stash and then inadvertently forgotten. He advises Tōta and Kurōmaru in dealing with the monsters.{{Ref|Chapter|Ch. 7, 8}} 1400 years ago, he achieved immortality by eating the flesh of mermaid, but he has weak regenerative powers, resulting in numerous body scars, and he is susceptible to being killed by beheading and some other toxins.{{Ref|Chapter|Ch. 9}} Despite his power and status within the organization, he's generally laid-back and has a reputation for being a slacker.

;{{nihongo|{{vanchor|Kirië Sakurame|Kirie Sakurame}}<!-- her name in the English version of the manga is with an ë -->|桜雨キリヱ|Sakurame Kirie}} <!-- anime profile 04 -->
: {{voiced by|[[Ai Kayano]]<ref name="Anime News Network 2"/>|Amanda Lee<ref name="English Cast List" />}}
: Member number 9, Kirië Sakurame is the leading patron of UQ Holder, residing in the penthouse suite of the premises. Although she appears as a little <!-- 10-year-old --> girl with orange blonde braided hair and glasses, she has lived much longer. Her ability is Reset and Restart, which allows her to rewind time, averting adverse events like her own death by returning to a specific instant in time marked by [[save point]]s.{{Ref|Chapter|Vol. 4}} She has also used this power to make a fortune in the stock market.{{volume needed|date=December 2017}} She can also bring along a person she touches, either just their mind or their body as well.{{Ref|Chapter|Ch. 36}} Kirië badmouths Tōta due to their bad start on their first mission together, but becomes more friendly with him afterwards.{{Ref|Chapter|Vol. 4}}

;{{nihongo|Santa Sasaki|佐々木 三太|Sasaki Santa}}
:Santa Sasaki is a student at Amano-Mihashira Academy City who lives as a ''[[hikkikomori]]'' (shut-in) in his dorm room, living off of [[real-money trading|real-money transactions in video games]]. He is aware of the UQ Holder members that infiltrated the school, but is surprised to find that Tōta and Kurōmaru have become his roommates. As a Psion, he has several abilities that the UQ Holder members call "unique skills" including intangibility (going through walls and putting people through walls), telekinesis, flight, and possession. Having been bullied as a student, he had died but was turned into a [[revenant]], a powerful vengeful spirit, by his friend, a necromancer named Sayoko. Assisted by Tōta and his friends, Santa stops Sayoko's plan and restores her to her original self, but she passes away soon after. Santa then joins UQ Holder as member number 12.{{Ref|Chapter|Ch. 43-56}}

; {{vanchor|Basago|バサゴ}} <!-- anime profile 11 -->
: {{voiced by|[[Tsubasa Yonaga]]<ref>http://uqholder.jp/character/</ref><!-- click profile 11 -->|[[Bryson Baugus]]<ref name="English Cast List" />}}
: A UQ Holder executive that Tōta and Kurōmaru meet.{{Ref|Chapter|Ch. 7}}

===''Negima'' characters===
{{Main|List of Negima characters}}
Some of the characters from the ''Negima'' series make appearances in this series.
<!-- List only the ones that are recurring and get volume profiles (e.g. Fate), not one-time or cameos -->

;{{nihongo|[[List of Negima! Magister Negi Magi characters#Fate Averruncus|Fate Averruncus]]|フェイト・アーウェルンクス}}
:{{voiced by|[[Akira Ishida]]<ref name="Negima Cast">{{cite web|url=http://uqholder.jp/staff-cast/|title=staff&cast}}</ref>|Daman Mills<ref name="English Cast List" />}}
:He was Negi Springfield's main rival and comrade in the ''Negima'' series, and is currently heralded as the greatest wizard in the Solar System. He leads "Ala Alba", the brigade Negi founded with his students. He opposes UQ Holder, claiming that Yukihime was responsible for Negi's disappearance, while UQ Holder regards him as its greatest enemy.{{Ref|Chapter|Vol. 4}} Fate claims that there is a way to save Negi and the entire Solar System by using Tōta,{{Ref|Chapter|Vol. 4}} but that he was also responsible for the death of Tōta's parents.{{Ref|Chapter|Vol. 5}}

;{{nihongo|[[List of Negima! Magister Negi Magi characters#Negi Springfield|Negi Springfield]]|ネギ・スプリングフィールド|Negi Supuringufīrudo}}
: {{voiced by|[[Rina Satō]]<ref name="Anime News Network 2"/>|[[Greg Ayres]]<ref name="English Cast List" />}}
: Tōta's grandfather. After his adventures in ''Negima'', Negi helped his former teacher, Yukihime, form UQ Holder and made a name for himself in the magical world where he is known as "The Greatest Mage." At first believed to be deceased, it is later revealed by Fate that Negi is still alive though his whereabouts are unknown. Unlike his former master and grandson, Negi possesses a complete version of Magia Erebea. He is eventually revealed to have been possessed by the Mage of the Beginning, who is slowly locking away his soul and gaining control of his body. It is also revealed in a video recording by Chamo that Negi confessed his love to Chisame who initially rejected him. Dana, however, shows Tōta and his group a picture of Negi and Chisame during their wedding and explains that they were married 7 years after Negi's victory over Ialda and after a lot of "twists and turns".

;{{nihongo|[[List of Negima! Magister Negi Magi characters#Mana Tatsumiya|Mana Tatsumiya]]|龍宮 真名|Tatsumiya Mana}}
:{{voiced by|Miho Sakuma<ref name="Negima Cast"/>|Katelyn Barr<ref name="English Cast List" />}}
: One of Negi Springfield's former students, she is acting director of the Amano-Mihashira Academy, filling up for some "old friend of hers". She has dark skin and uses magic pistols to fight, able to defeat Tōta when they first meet. She appears fairly young as she ages much slower than a normal human.{{Ref|Chapter|Vol. 7}}

;{{nihongo|[[List of Negima! Magister Negi Magi characters#Nagi Springfield|Nagi Springfield]]|ナギ・スプリングフィールド|Nagi Supuringufīrudo}}
:{{voiced by|[[Takehito Koyasu]]<ref name="ep11">{{cite episode | title= Her Love Story| series=UQ Holder| number= 11|network=Tokyo MX | date=December 11, 2017 | time=Ending credits}}</ref>|Alan Brincks<ref name="English Cast List" />}}
:Negi's father and Tōta's great-grandfather. A legendary mage known as "The Thousand Master," he led the group "Ala Rubra" during the Great War a hundred years ago that was started by the Mage of the Beginning. He reappears in an illusion alongside his son, Negi, before members of UQ Holder and Fate. It was later revealed that he was possessed by the Lifemaker, forcing his son, Negi, to defeat him and in turn become possessed himself, unlike what happened in the original dimension from ''Negima!'' in which Negi managed to defeat the Lifemaker while saving him in the process with Ala Alba's help, and he married Evangeline afterwards.

;{{nihongo|[[List of Negima! Magister Negi Magi characters#Ayaka Yukihiro|Ayaka Yukihiro]]|雪広 あやか|Yukihiro Ayaka}}
:{{voiced by|[[Junko Minagawa]]<ref name="Negima Cast"/>|[[Shelley Calene-Black]], Cat Thomas (Young)<ref name="English Cast List" />}}
:One of Negi Springfield's former students and leader of the Yukihiro Conglomerate, she reappears now as an aged woman with her great-granddaughter, Mizore as guests of Yukihime. She meets with and becomes fond of Tōta due him being Negi's grandson. Ayaka also still possesses her pactio card that she made with Negi decades ago.

;{{nihongo|[[List of Negima! Magister Negi Magi characters#Chachamaru Karakuri|Chachamaru Karakuri]]|絡繰 茶々丸|Karakuri Chachamaru}}
:{{voiced by|[[Akeno Watanabe]]<ref name="Negima Cast"/>|Joanne Bonasso<ref name="English Cast List" />}}
:One of Negi Springfield's former students and partners who was once Yukihime's servant. She reappears alongside Ayaka, whom she is now in service of.

;{{nihongo|[[List of Negima! Magister Negi Magi characters#Sayo Aisaka|Sayo Aisaka]]|相坂 さよ|Aisaka Sayo}}
:{{voiced by|[[Yuri Shiratori]]<ref name="Negima Cast"/>|[[Kira Vincent-Davis]]<ref name="English Cast List" />}}
:One of Negi Springfield's former students and a ghost. Being a ghost, her appearance has remained unchanged in the following decades after the events of Negima. She reappears alongside Ayaka and Zazie to greet Tōta.

;{{nihongo|[[List of Negima! Magister Negi Magi characters#Zazie Rainyday|Zazie Rainyday]]|ザジ・レイニーデイ|Zaji Reinīdei}}
:One of Negi Springfield's former students and the princess of the Demon Kind. Similar to Mana, she ages much slower than a normal human and has not changed much in terms of appearance. She appears before Tōta with Sayo and Ayaka to greet him.

;{{nihongo|[[List of Negima! Magister Negi Magi characters#Ayase Yue|Yue Ayase]]|綾瀬 夕映|Ayase Yue}}
:{{voiced by|[[Natsuko Kuwatani]]<ref name="Negima Cast"/>|Elissa Cuellar<ref name="English Cast List" />}}
:One of Negi Springfield's former students and partners who is now known as Yue "The All-Knowing" and "The Magical Detective". Believed to have been killed in the previous war along with her best friend, Nodoka, Jack, and Albireo, the four reappear with Negi in front of UQ Holder to take Tōta away.

;{{nihongo|[[List of Negima! Magister Negi Magi characters#Miyazaki Nodoka|Nodoka Miyazaki]]|宮崎 のどか|Miyazaki Nodoka}}
:{{voiced by|[[Mamiko Noto]]<ref name="Negima Cast"/>|[[Sasha Paysinger]]<ref name="English Cast List" />}}
:One of Negi Springfield's former students and partners who was the most romantically involved with him of her class 70 years ago. Known in the magical world as Nodoka "The All-Perceiving" and "The Mind Reader". Believed to have been killed in the previous war along with her best friend, Yue, Jack, and Albireo, the four reappear with Negi in front of UQ Holder to take Tōta away.

;{{nihongo|[[List of Negima! Magister Negi Magi characters#Albireo Imma|Albireo Imma]]|アルビレオ・イマ|Arubireo Ima}}
:{{voiced by|[[Daisuke Ono]]<ref name="Negima Cast"/>|[[David Wald]]<ref name="English Cast List" />}}
:Also known as the "Librian of a Thousand Faces, he was a former member of Ala Rubra with a high proficiency for gravity magic who took on the pseudonym "Ku:nel Sanders". It is said that his magical prowess is equal to that of Yukihime's. Believed to have been killed in the previous war along with Nodoka, Yue, and Jack, the four reappear with Negi in front of UQ Holder to take Tōta away.{{Ref|Chapter|Ch. 127}} Tota is using Imma's gravity blade.{{Ref|Chapter|Ch. 38}}

;{{nihongo|[[List of Negima! Magister Negi Magi characters#Jack Rakan|Jack Rakan]]|ジャック・ラカン|Jakku Rakan}}
:{{anime voices|[[Rikiya Koyama]]<ref name="ANN3"/>|[[John Swasey]]<ref name="English Cast List" />}}
:Also known as "Rakan of the Thousand Blades" and a former member of Ala Rubra was once considered a rival to Nagi Springfield. Believed to have been killed in the previous war along with Yue, Albireo, and Nodoka, the four reappear with Negi in front of UQ Holder to take Tōta away.

;{{nihongo|[[List of Negima! Magister Negi Magi characters#Asuna Kagurazaka|Asuna Kagurazaka]]|神楽坂 明日菜|Kagurazaka Asuna}}
:{{voiced by|[[Akemi Kanda]]<ref name="Negima Cast"/><!-- anime profile 15 -->|[[Luci Christian]]<ref name="English Cast List" />}}
:One of Negi's former students and his very first partner. She had a natural ability to cancel any kind of magic, a trait that was transferred to Tōta, who is a clone created not only with Negi's abilities, but hers as well. It is said that she is already dead, but she appears in a flashback created by Albireo for Tōta to know all the truth and finally choose a side to support. She introduces herself to Tōta as his grandmother and ultimately helps him find the resolve to fight the Lifemaker-possessed Negi.

;{{nihongo|[[List of Negima! Magister Negi Magi characters#Albert Chamomile|Albert Chamomile]]|カモミール・アルベール|Kamomīru Arubēru}} / {{nihongo|Chamo|カモ|Kamo}} 
:An old, talking ermine and Negi's longtime friend, he was entrusted by Negi to watch over one of his workshops in Kyoto. He has the ability to transform into a human with high fighting prowess, but still retains his perverted demeanor from his young days.

===Other groups and characters===
;{{nihongo|Shinobu Yuuki|結城 忍|Yūki Shinobu}} <!-- anime profile 06 -->
:{{voiced by|[[Sayaka Harada]]<ref name="Anime News Network 3">{{cite news|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2017-08-04/uq-holder-anime-reveals-teaser-video-more-cast-theme-song-artists/.119744|title=UQ Holder Anime Reveals Teaser Video, More Cast, Theme Song Artists|work=Anime News Network|date=August 4, 2017|accessdate=August 4, 2017}}</ref>|[[Tia Ballard]]<ref name="English Cast List" />}}
:A young girl Tōta befriends during his travels, Shinobu dreams of competing in the Neo Olympics as a racer.{{Ref|Chapter|Ch. 2}} Shinobu later reunites with Tōta at the UQ Holder Headquarters where she starts working as part of the staff.{{volume needed|date=December 2017}} She is similar in name and appearance with Shinobu Maehara, a character from Akamatsu's work ''[[Love Hina]]''.{{original research inline|date=December 2017}}{{citation needed|reason=need source that says she is based on shinobu from love hina|date=December 2017}}

; {{vanchor|Powerful Hand|PMSCS}}
: Powerful Hand is a group of immortal hunter mercenaries working for the Private Military & Security Company (PMSCS). They include: {{Nihongo|Shion Nagumo|南雲士音|Nagumo Shion}},<!-- anime profile 12 --> a blind swordsman; {{Nihongo|Kaito|灰斗}},<!-- anime profile 13 --> a martial artist werewolf who taught Tota the shundo technique; and {{Nihongo|Chao Xinxai|超星仔}},<!--Also Xinzqai from vol. 2, but changed to Xinxai in vol. 3 English manga,  anime profile 14 -->{{Ref|Chapter|Vol. 3 profiles}} a wizard specialist in shadow puppets.{{Ref|Chapter|Ch. 20}}

; Sayoko 
: A schoolmate at Amano-Mihashira Academy, she was bullied by students and had died, turning into a ''[[onryō]]'', a vengeful spirit. She is the cause of the murders on the campus including the ones eight years prior to Santa and Tota's meeting. She is also the [[necromancer]] who turned her friend Santa into a [[revenant]] and gave him the Psion abilities. Hoping to get rid of the bullies and scum of society, she takes Santa's wishes by concoting a virus that leads to a worldwide [[zombie apocalypse]].{{Ref|Chapter|Ch. 48-56}}

;{{nihongo|Dana Ananga Jagannatha|ダーナ・アナンガ・ジャガンナータ |Dāna Ananga Jagannāta}}
:Also known as the {{nihongo|Witch of the Rift|狭間の魔女|Hazama no Majo}}, she is a true, natural born vampire, unlike Evangeline and Tōta who obtained their vampiric traits by magic, thus her powers are far greater, capable of instantly regenerating herself from any damage and her powers allow her to perform higher feats such as opening rifts in the space-time continuum. She was Evangeline's master when she was younger, but somehow they currently have a strained relationship, and takes Tōta, Kirie and Santa to train under her for a while as well.

;{{nihongo|Ialda Baoth|ヨルダ・バオト|Yoruda Baoto}}
:{{voiced by|[[Yuko Kaida]]<ref name="ep11"/>|Joanne Bonasso<ref name="English Cast List" />}}
:The main antagonist of the series and an immortal mage responsible for transforming Evangeline into a vampire 700 years ago and the instigator of the war on Inverse Mars a hundred years ago. Most famously, known as The Mage of the Beginning and The Lifemaker, she appears to have an interest in Touta. It's said that she is currently possessing Negi's body, just like she once possessed Nagi's body before he was destroyed by his son, and thus Fate looks desperately for a way to remove her from his body without killing him since then, while Yukihime seeks to uphold her promise to kill him should she ever obtain control of his body.

;{{nihongo|Honoka and Isana Konoe}}
:Granddaughters of Konoka Konoe who are part of Fate's new Ala Alba. They appear before Tōta with the intention to convince him to join their ranks.

;{{nihongo|Mizore Yukihiro|雪広 みぞれ|Yukihiro Mizore}} <!-- anime profile 07 -->
:{{voiced by|[[Akari Kitō]]<ref name="Anime News Network 3">{{cite news|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2017-08-04/uq-holder-anime-reveals-teaser-video-more-cast-theme-song-artists/.119744|title=UQ Holder Anime Reveals Teaser Video, More Cast, Theme Song Artists|work=Anime News Network|date=August 4, 2017|accessdate=August 4, 2017}}</ref>|[[Juliet Simmons]]<ref name="English Cast List" />}}
:Great-granddaughter of Ayaka Yukihiro and heir to the Yukihiro Conglomerate who wishes to marry Tōta. Like Ayaka, Mizore has a very proud personality but is also a very kind girl at heart.

;{{nihongo|Tena Vita|テナ・ヴィタ|Vuīta Tena}}
:{{voiced by|[[Rena Maeda]]<ref name="ep11"/>|[[Margaret McDonald (voice actress)|Margaret McDonald]]<ref name="English Cast List" />}}
:Also known as {{nihongo|Cutlass|カトラス|Katorasu}}, a mysterious girl who heralds herself as Tōta's sister but harbors a strong hatred towards him. She is armed with ''Ensis Exorcizans'', the pactio weapon used by Asuna in ''Negima!'', with the ability to exorcise demons and dispel magic, and in Cutlass' case, summon lightning magic, implying that she is an Asuna/Negi hybrid clone just like Tōta, albeit with incomplete powers. On the Chapter 141 it was revealed that her birth name is ''Amater Magic Laboratory Immortal Experiment 17''.

==Media==

===Manga===
{{main|List of UQ Holder! chapters}}

''UQ Holder!'' is a Japanese [[manga]] series written and illustrated by [[Ken Akamatsu]]. It began its serialization in the manga magazine ''[[Weekly Shōnen Magazine]]'' on August 28, 2013. Its individual chapters have been collected into seventeen ''[[tankōbon]]'' volumes by [[Kodansha]], the first released on December 17, 2013. The series is licensed for English language release in North America by [[Kodansha USA|Kodansha Comics]], who published the first volume on March 18, 2014. As the series is published in Japan, it is also released simultaneously in English digitally by [[Crunchyroll]]. In October 2016, the series changed magazines from the ''Weekly Shōnen Magazine'' to the ''[[Bessatsu Shōnen Magazine]]'',<ref name="AnimeAnc"/> and was renamed ''UQ Holder!: Magister Negi Magi! 2'' starting with the November 2016 issue.<ref name="subtitle"/>

===Anime===
An [[anime]] adaptation of the manga was announced in the ''[[Weekly Shōnen Magazine]]'''s 30th issue of 2016,<ref name="AnimeAnc">{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2016-06-18/negima-spinoff-manga-uq-holder-gets-anime/.103359|title=Negima Spinoff Manga UQ Holder! Gets Anime|date=June 18, 2016|website=[[Anime News Network]]|accessdate=June 18, 2016}}</ref> later revealed to be a television series and OAD.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/daily-briefs/2016-12-23/uq-holder-manga-creator-ken-akamatsu-teases-tv-anime-anime-dvd-in-2017/.110265|title=UQ Holder Manga Creator Ken Akamatsu Teases TV Anime, Anime DVD in 2017|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|date=December 23, 2016|accessdate=December 23, 2016}}</ref> Youhei Suzuki is directing the anime at [[J.C.Staff]], Akamatsu himself is handling the series composition alongside Shogo Yasukawa, EGG FIRM is producing the series and the main cast from the original ''Negima!'' anime returns.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2017-03-17/uq-holder-tv-anime-reveals-october-debut-visual-cast-staff/.113593|title=UQ Holder! TV Anime Reveals October Debut, Visual, Cast, Staff|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|date=March 18, 2017|accessdate=March 18, 2017}}</ref> The OAD will be released on September 8, 2017, while the television series premiered on October 2, 2017.<ref name="ANN3"/> Two more OAD's will be released with the manga's 16th and 17th volumes.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2017-09-23/uq-holder-magister-negi-magi-2-manga-gets-2-more-original-anime-dvds/.121776|title=UQ Holder! Magister Negi Magi! 2 Manga Gets 2 More Original Anime DVDs|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|date=September 23, 2017|accessdate=September 23, 2017}}</ref> The series ran for 12 episodes.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://uqholder.jp/products/|title=BD/DVD}}</ref>

[[Sentai Filmworks]] has licensed the series and simulcast the anime on [[Amazon (company)|Amazon]]'s Anime Strike streaming channel in the U.S. and in other selected digital services elsewhere.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2017-09-25/sentai-filmworks-licenses-uq-holder-anime-for-anime-strike-simulcast/.121850|title=Sentai Filmworks Licenses UQ Holder! Anime For Anime Strike Simulcast|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|accessdate=September 25, 2017|date=September 25, 2017}}</ref> [[MVM Films]] acquired the series for home video release in the UK.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://twitter.com/MVM_UK/status/924277651505807361?p=v|title=Here's the last of our announcements. Confirming we are releasing No Game, No Life: Zero movie. Also UQ Holder and Vatican Miracle Examiner.|publisher=[[Twitter.com]]|accessdate=October 28, 2017}}</ref> [[Madman Entertainment]] acquired the series for distribution in Australia and New Zealand,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://dealerguide.madman.com.au/releases/46155|title=Uq Holder Complete Series (Blu-ray)|publisher=[[Madman Entertainment]]|accessdate=October 29, 2018}}</ref> and simulcasted the series on AnimeLab.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.animelab.com/blog/animelab-fall-simulcast-lineup-2017/|title=AnimeLab Fall Simulcast Lineup 2017|last=Bortignon|first=Tegan|date=October 1, 2017|accessdate=October 29, 2018}}</ref>

